parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and leaking of the fuel tank can cause fuel to spill, leading to a fire hazard, and potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
strong chemical fumes
fuel spills when filling the tank
gas tank cracks
fuel tank failure
and inability to pass state inspection.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Inadequate repairs to the fuel tank can lead to continued fuel leaks, fire hazards, and potentially serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
strong chemical fumes
fuel spills when filling the tank
gas tank cracks
fuel tank failure
and inadequate repair work by dealerships.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure to honor the recall can lead to continued fuel leaks, fire hazards, and potentially serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
strong chemical fumes
fuel spills when filling the tank
gas tank cracks
fuel tank failure
and dealerships or manufacturers refusing to repair or replace the fuel tank.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, resulting in property damage and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The ignition switch is inoperative
the key gets stuck in the ignition switch
the vehicle won't turn off
the engine check light comes on and off
the vehicle shuts down while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the alternator can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, resulting in property damage and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The alternator catches on fire
smoke comes from under the hood
the vehicle shuts down while driving
the electrical system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to catch on fire, resulting in property damage and potential harm to occupants.
symptoms: The electrical system fails
the vehicle catches on fire
smoke comes from under the hood
the ignition module fails
the wiring harness wires short.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle can cause the seat belt to not latch or stay engaged, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle does not latch
the seat belt will not stay engaged
the spring in the buckle is broken
the buckle pops open with warning
the latch on the buckle is broken
the seat belt is difficult to latch
the seat belt will not tighten
the seat belt loosens while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to not retract or lock properly, which can lead to serious injury or death in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt retractor does not retract
the seat belt does not lock
the seat belt will not stay engaged
the seat belt is difficult to latch
the seat belt loosens while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Rear Seat Shoulder Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of rear seat shoulder belts can increase the risk of injury or death to rear seat occupants, particularly children, in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The vehicle is not equipped with rear seat shoulder belts
making it difficult to safely install a booster seat or restrain a child.
